<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 6:33PM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Cherokee and Monroe Counties through 715 PM EDT...
At 633 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Madisonville, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Madisonville, Vonore, Tellico Plains, Fort Loudon State Park, Coker
Creek, Violet, Tariffville, McGee Carson Peninsula, Hiawasse Dam and
Citico Beach.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
